# How does the mortality rate vary across different countries/regions?

mortality_rate=cor_vir.groupby('Country/Region')[['Confirmed','Deaths']].sum().sort_values(by=['Confirmed','Deaths'],ascending=False)
df=(mortality_rate['Deaths']/mortality_rate['Confirmed'])*100
plt.figure(figsize=(30,8))
df.sort_values(ascending=False).plot(kind='bar')
plt.xlabel('Country/Region',fontweight='bold',size=23)
plt.ylabel('Mortality Rate',fontweight='bold',size=23)
plt.title('Mortality Rate over different Country/Regions',fontweight='bold',size=23)
plt.show()

# How does the recovery rate vary across different countries/regions?

recovery_rate=cor_vir.groupby('Country/Region')[['Confirmed','Recovered']].sum()
rec_rate1=(recovery_rate['Recovered']/recovery_rate['Confirmed'])*100
plt.figure(figsize=(30,8))
rec_rate1.sort_values(ascending=False).plot(kind='bar')
plt.title('Recovery Rate over different Country/Regions',fontweight='bold',style='oblique',size=23)
plt.xlabel('Country/Regions',fontweight='bold',style='oblique',size=23)
plt.ylabel('Recovery Rate',fontweight='bold',style='oblique',size=23)
plt.xticks(rotation=90)
plt.show()
In [675]:
# What is the trend of new confirmed cases over time globally?

plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
cor_vir['ObservationDate'] = pd.to_datetime(cor_vir['ObservationDate'])
new_confirmed=cor_vir.groupby('ObservationDate')['Confirmed'].sum().reset_index()
new_confirmed['New Confirmed Cases']=new_confirmed['Confirmed'].diff()
plt.plot(new_confirmed['ObservationDate'],new_confirmed['New Confirmed Cases'],color='crimson')
plt.title('Trend of New Confirmed Cases ',fontweight='bold',style='oblique',size=10)
plt.xlabel('Observation Date',fontweight='bold',style='oblique',size=10)
plt.ylabel('New Confirmed Cases',fontweight='bold',style='oblique',size=10)
plt.show()
In [33]:
# How does the fatality rate vary across different provinces/states?

prov_rate=cor_vir.groupby('Province/State')[['Confirmed','Deaths']].sum()
prov_rate['Fatality Rate']=(prov_rate['Deaths']/prov_rate['Confirmed'])*100
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
prov_rate['Fatality Rate'].sort_values(ascending=False).plot(kind='line',color='red')
plt.title('Fatality rate across different Provinces/States',fontweight='bold',style='oblique',size=15)
plt.xlabel('Provinces/States',fontweight='bold',style='oblique',size=10)
plt.ylabel('Fatality Rate',fontweight='bold',style='oblique',size=10)
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.show()

In [706]:
# What is the trend of active cases over time globally?

act_cases = cor_vir.groupby('ObservationDate')[['Confirmed', 'Deaths', 'Recovered']].sum().reset_index()
act_cases['Active Cases'] = act_cases['Confirmed'] - act_cases['Deaths'] - act_cases['Recovered']
plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
plt.plot(act_cases['ObservationDate'],act_cases['Active Cases'],color='darksalmon')
plt.title('Trend of active cases over time globally',fontweight='bold',size=10)
plt.xlabel('Observation Date',fontweight='bold',size=10)
plt.ylabel('Number of Active Cases',fontweight='bold',size=10)
plt.xticks(rotation=60)
plt.show()
